{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "23", "m": "03", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "12", "M": "38", "S": "36"}}, "news": [{"title": "Lucknow civic body's budget 2026 okays no hike in property tax", "para": "Lucknow Municipal Corporation approved a Rs 1,253 crore budget for 2026-27, focusing on development without increasing property tax or parking charges. The civic body aims to boost revenue through better tax collection and expanding the tax base, with funds allocated for infrastructure improvements, sanitation, and beautification projects across all wards.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/lucknow-municipal-corporation-approves-2026-27-budget-with-no-property-tax-hike/129741802?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-84008/129741802.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Over 500 objects to proposed collector guideline rates for property in Indore", "para": "Nearly 500 objections were filed against proposed collector guideline rate hikes in Indore, with citizens and experts deeming increases unrealistic. Concerns include blanket hikes for bypass-adjacent land, outdated apartment valuations, and prohibitive costs for villages near new road projects. The District Evaluation Committee will review these complaints before forwarding the final proposal to Bhopal.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/controversial-100-hike-sparks-over-500-objections-to-indore-collector-guideline-rates/129741777?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-20288/129741777.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Allotment of plots in new industrial areas of Indore region to begin from April", "para": "The Madhya Pradesh Industrial Development Corporation will begin allotting plots in nine new industrial areas across the Indore region from April. These developments aim to attract investments in sectors like food processing, confectionery, and plastics, bolstering MSME-driven industries. The expansion includes a large township at Bardari and several smaller clusters to support business growth.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/indore-to-launch-new-industrial-zones-by-april-boosting-msme-growth/129741713?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1563216/129741713.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}